    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-03-12T15:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-03-12T15:44:00-05:00" n="57"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <head>57. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d57fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, DEF 19 <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET Secret; Priority. Drafted
                        by <persName corresp="#p_WCB1">Wood</persName> and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BRW1">Barnett</persName>, in <gloss target="#t_AID1"
                            >AID</gloss> by <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">Stoneman</persName>, and in
                            <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_ISA1">ISA</gloss>
                        by <persName corresp="#p_KCJR1">Colonel Kent</persName>. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_POLAD1"
                            >POLAD</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1963-03-12T15:44:00-05:00">March 12, 1963, 3:44 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>856. Joint State/<gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_AID1"
                        >AID</gloss>. References: 1) Embassy Airgram A-417;<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d57fn2">Airgram A-417 from Saigon, February 8, enclosed three copies
                        of the Comprehensive Plan for South Vietnam, and indicated that “the
                        Ambassador has concurred in the Plan as a basis for <gloss target="#t_MAP1"
                            >MAP</gloss> planning.” (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>)</note>) <gloss
                        target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 800.<note n="3" xml:id="d57fn3">
                        <ref target="#d53">Document 53</ref>.</note> The Joint Chiefs of Staff have
                    recommended that the Comprehensive Plan for South Viet-Nam (<gloss
                        target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss>) be approved as the basis for refinement of
                    the <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 64 <gloss target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> and
                    development of the <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 65-69 Military Assistance
                    Plan for Viet-Nam.<note n="4" xml:id="d57fn4">See <ref target="#d51">Document
                            51</ref>.</note> Require ASAP specific Country Team recommendations
                    concerning the <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss> in view of following
                    factors: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Imminence presentation <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 64 <gloss
                                target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> to Congress (estimated April). If
                                State/<gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_AID1"
                                >AID</gloss> decide accept <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss>,
                            presentation may be affected.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Fact that most significant cost increase under <gloss
                                target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss> (approximately $75 million) over
                            dollar guidelines occurs in <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 64.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Fact that detailed review of 64 Program is scheduled at <gloss
                                target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> in April.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>Stated urgency some of the requirements for activations under the
                            increased <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 64 force levels proposed in
                                <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>(5)</label>
                        <item>Likelihood that to attain objectives of the <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1"
                                >CPSVN</gloss> requires parallel development of other mutually
                            supporting national plans and programs. To enable State/<gloss
                                target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>
                            expedite decision whether accept <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss>
                            for planning, request Country Team views or estimates concerning
                            following: <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> willingness make the
                                    required additional financial contribution. Realize that <gloss
                                        target="#t_CT1">CT</gloss> may judge that direct approaches
                                    to <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> now proposing additional
                                        <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> deficit or other fiscal
                                    measures might adversely affect current negotiations re <gloss
                                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> contribution counterinsurgency
                                    funds. If this is case, request <gloss target="#t_CT1"
                                        >CT</gloss> judgment (without <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                                        >GVN</gloss> consultation) what portion of additional
                                    required piaster financing <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>
                                    would accept. If this is less than total 846 million piasters,
                                    request general outline of the modification of the <gloss
                                        target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss> that would be necessary and
                                    revision of total dollar costs for <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                                        >FY</gloss> 64 that would result.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>Para 3e of the <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss>
                                    indicates <gloss target="#t_CIDG1">CIDG</gloss> personnel may be
                                    absorbed into National Police during “phase down”. Can we assume
                                    plans that must be developed as described <gloss
                                        target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 800 so provide?</item>
                                <pb facs="0175" n="149" xml:id="pg_149"/>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>Requirements for dollar purchase of piasters for construction
                                    indicated in <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss> for <gloss
                                        target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 64 and subsequent years and
                                    feasibility construction with local currency not affecting gold
                                    outflow?</item>
                                <label>4.</label>
                                <item>Is there provision in the <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1"
                                        >CPSVN</gloss> for a <gloss target="#t_MAP1"
                                        >MAP</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>
                                    “maintenance” cost for villages and hamlets secured under <gloss
                                        target="#t_CIDG1">CIDG</gloss> program after they pass to
                                    the strategic hamlet program?</item>
                                <label>5.</label>
                                <item>What revisions current political economic programs would be
                                    required if <gloss target="#t_CPSVN1">CPSVN</gloss>
                                    approved?</item>
                                <label>6.</label>
                                <item>What would be economic consequences if additional 846 million
                                    piasters provided through <gloss target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>
                                    deficit financing?<note n="5" xml:id="d57fn5">In telegram 857 to
                                        Saigon, March 12, the Embassy was asked for additional
                                        comment on the Comprehensive Plan: <p>“State requests frank
                                                <gloss target="#t_TFSAIGON1">TF/Saigon</gloss> view
                                            on whether plan should be changed to extend phase out
                                            U.S. forces by one year (<gloss target="#t_FY1"
                                                >FY</gloss> 65 through 68 rather than <gloss
                                                target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 65 through 67).</p>
                                        <p>“In requesting this view we have in mind that such
                                            stretch out would</p>
                                        <p>“a) require smaller increase in <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                                                >FY</gloss> 64 training costs to U.S. and <gloss
                                                target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss>;</p>
                                        <p>“b) lessen risk inability <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                                                >GVN</gloss> take over in <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                                                >FY</gloss> 67;</p>
                                        <p>“c) reduce political risk that <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                                                >GVN</gloss> become unduly concerned that U.S.
                                            planning pull out.” (Department of State, Central Files,
                                            DEF 19 <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET)</p>
                                    </note>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
